				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Decent Song<a name="36430"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 26 04 12:15 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Just to clear up a misconception here...
<br />

<br />
It is the knockback effect that causes spell interruption, not the actual damage.  I know this in specific because one trick I've used before with my wizard when someone did a bad pull and we were going to wipe is to put my back to a corner before casting evac.  Even though I may have been taking hits, I wasn't getting knocked backwards, so casting wasn't interrupted and we all lived through the experience.  
<br />

<br />
The reason any song/spell with knockback isn't allways effective is because the caster has a counter-skill that allows them to have a chance to continue even though they moved.  However, some chance to interrupt is still better than no chance.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Koda Kyrie, Guild Leader of Molto Espressivo, Firiona Vie server</span></td>
