				<td colspan="2"><span>Spell casting works something like this, atleast to my experience when bored on an alt.
<br />

<br />
When you begin casting a spell, it records your loc, when you end it checks against it. Skills somehow make it so the locs can be slightly different.
<br />

<br />
Try this out. Start casting a long casting spell (with a caster) with your back in a corner. Then run around a bit, and before your song ends, put your back back in the corner, and it will finish, even though youmoved.</span></td>
